# Plugins: how to ask something to the user
We will see a simple plugin that, when a site invokes our function, asks something to the user and then takes some actions.

```python
from Plugin import PluginManager

@PluginManager.registerTo("UiWebsocket")
class UiWebsocketPlugin(object):
    def _get_number(self, to):
        self.response(to, 101)

    def actionGetNumber(self, to):
        self.cmd("confirm", ["Are you sure you want a number?", "Yeah, Sure"], lambda (res): self._get_number(to))
```

The commands that you can issue to ask something to the user [are documented on zeronet.io/docs](https://zeronet.io/docs/site_development/zeroframe_api_reference/) and are "confirm" to ask a yes/no question, "notification" to only say something to the user, "prompt" to allow the user to insert text.

# Plugin: creating a new permission and API calls
We will create our new permissions "numbers" to call our previous function numbers.

```python
@PluginManager.registerTo("UiWebsocket")
class UiWebsocketPlugin(object):
    # What to do when our permission is added
    def actionPermissionAdd(self, to, permission):
        super(UiWebsocketPlugin, self).actionPermissionAdd(to, permission)
        if permission == "numbers":
            pass # Or do something if you have to. Remember that self.site points to the site which page we are currently viewing.

    # We return a description of our permission
    def actionPermissionDetails(self, to, permission):
        if permission != "numbers":
            return super(UiWebsocketPlugin, self).actionPermissionDetails(self, to, permission)
        self.response(to, "Allows to call the numbers action, which gives you a delicious number")

    # Our action that should check for permission
    def actionNumbers(self, to):
        if "numbers" in self.site.settings["permissions"]:
            self.response(to, 101)
        else:
            self.response(to, {"error": "You don't have permission for this command"})
```

The code is self-esplicative, but note that you have to do explicit permission check in your command.

This article is part of [[The Truth about ZeroNet]] series of tutorials.

